`chatId = ids.find((id) => /^(oc|chat|group|room|c)_/i.test(id))`. `ou_` doesn't match `oc|chat|group|room|c`. So chatId is not the open ID. Then `userId = userIdFromSessionIds(platform, ids)`. For feishu, this returns `ids.find((id) => isFeishuUnionUserId(id))`. `isFeishuUnionUserId` checks `/^on_/i` or `/^union/i`. So `ou_X` doesn't match → userId is undefined. So parsed = `{chatId: 'oc_chat', userId: undefined}`.

Then `routingUserIdFromSessionKey` falls back to find `ou_` in the ids. So it returns the open ID. Good.

