`deliverTask` (target side, local case):
```ts
async deliverTask(teamSlug, dispatchId, result) {
  const collabTask = this.collabBoard.getTask(dispatchId);
  ...
  // completedTask found on target (status 'done') ✓

  const isLocalOrigin = await this.isLocalTeam(collabTask.fromTeam);
  if (isLocalOrigin) {
    await this.handleLocalResponse(response);  // calls applyResponse
  }

  // AFTER handleLocalResponse:
  const deliveredTask = this.collabBoard.transition({
    dispatchId,
    expected: ['in_progress', 'accepted', 'revision'],
    next: 'delivered',
    ...
  });
```

Wait! The `handleLocalResponse(response)` is called BEFORE the collabBoard.transition to 'delivered'. So when applyResponse runs, the collabBoard status is still 'in_progress', NOT 'delivered'. So even if applyResponse didn't return early (shadowTask existed), the check `collabTask.status === 'delivered'` would be FALSE because the transition hasn't happened yet.

So the auto-approve in applyResponse has TWO bugs:
1. shadowTask doesn't exist on origin → returns early (never reaches the auto-approve check).
2. Even if it did reach, collabBoard.status is 'in_progress' (not yet 'delivered') because the transition happens AFTER applyResponse.

So the auto-approve is doubly dead code. Definitively a bug.

Wait, let me re-read the order in deliverTask:

```ts
const isLocalOrigin = await this.isLocalTeam(collabTask.fromTeam);
    if (isLocalOrigin) {
      await this.handleLocalResponse(response);   // (A) applyResponse runs here
    } else if (this.redis) {
      await this.redis.xadd(...)                    // (B) remote: push to stream
    }

    // Update local collab board
